   "source": [
    "# 4.\tGive an example of when False positive is more crucial than false negative and vice versa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "19ab38b0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Yep — this is about which mistake is more costly in a classification problem.\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive vs False Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "First, quick meaning:\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive (FP): Model says Yes / Positive, but actually it is No / Negative\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative (FN): Model says No / Negative, but actually it is Yes / Positive\n",
    "\n",
    "Example in disease testing:\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive: test says person has disease, but actually does not\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative: test says person does not have disease, but actually does\n",
    "\n",
    "1) Example where False Positive is more crucial\n",
    "Spam email filter\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose the model classifies emails as:\n",
    "\n",
    "Spam\n",
    "\n",
    "Not Spam\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive here:\n",
    "\n",
    "A genuine important email is marked as spam.\n",
    "\n",
    "Why this is crucial:\n",
    "\n",
    "You may miss:\n",
    "\n",
    "job offer\n",
    "\n",
    "interview mail\n",
    "\n",
    "bank alert\n",
    "\n",
    "client communication\n",
    "\n",
    "This can create serious problems.\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative here:\n",
    "\n",
    "A spam email enters inbox.\n",
    "\n",
    "That is annoying, but often less harmful than losing an important real email.\n",
    "\n",
    "Conclusion:\n",
    "\n",
    "In spam filtering, False Positive is more crucial because blocking a genuine email is costlier than letting one spam email pass.\n",
    "\n",
    "Another good example: Facial recognition for phone unlock\n",
    "False Positive:\n",
    "\n",
    "Wrong person gets access to the phone.\n",
    "\n",
    "That is a serious security issue.\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative:\n",
    "\n",
    "Actual owner is denied once and tries again.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is inconvenient, but less dangerous.\n",
    "\n",
    "So here too, False Positive is more critical.\n",
    "\n",
    "2) Example where False Negative is more crucial\n",
    "Disease diagnosis / cancer detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Suppose a model predicts:\n",
    "\n",
    "Disease present\n",
    "\n",
    "Disease absent\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative:\n",
    "\n",
    "The model says healthy, but the person actually has cancer.\n",
    "\n",
    "Why this is crucial:\n",
    "\n",
    "disease goes untreated\n",
    "\n",
    "treatment gets delayed\n",
    "\n",
    "risk can become life-threatening\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive:\n",
    "\n",
    "The model says disease present, but actually person is healthy.\n",
    "\n",
    "This causes:\n",
    "\n",
    "stress\n",
    "\n",
    "extra tests\n",
    "\n",
    "cost\n",
    "\n",
    "But usually this is still better than missing a real disease.\n",
    "\n",
    "Conclusion:\n",
    "\n",
    "In medical diagnosis, False Negative is more crucial because missing a real patient is far more dangerous.\n",
    "\n",
    "Another example: Fraud detection\n",
    "False Negative:\n",
    "\n",
    "A fraudulent transaction is marked as genuine.\n",
    "\n",
    "Result:\n",
    "\n",
    "money loss\n",
    "\n",
    "security issue\n",
    "\n",
    "customer trust damage\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive:\n",
    "\n",
    "A genuine transaction is blocked.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is inconvenient, but can often be fixed by verification.\n",
    "\n",
    "So in many fraud systems, False Negative is more dangerous.\n",
    "\n",
    "Simple rule to remember\n",
    "False Positive is more important when:\n",
    "\n",
    "Wrongly allowing or accusing something causes more damage.\n",
    "\n",
    "Examples:\n",
    "\n",
    "spam filtering\n",
    "\n",
    "face unlock\n",
    "\n",
    "judicial/police identification in some contexts\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative is more important when:\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing a real positive case is more dangerous.\n",
    "\n",
    "Examples:\n",
    "\n",
    "disease detection\n",
    "\n",
    "fraud detection\n",
    "\n",
    "fire alarm / security threat detection\n",
    "\n",
    "Beginner version\n",
    "\n",
    "Think like this:\n",
    "\n",
    "False Positive = alarm raised by mistake\n",
    "\n",
    "False Negative = real problem missed\n",
    "\n",
    "Now ask:\n",
    "\n",
    "Which is worse in this problem — a false alarm, or missing the real issue?\n",
    "\n",
    "That gives the answer.\n",
    "\n",
    "Interview answer in 5 lines\n",
    "\n",
    "A false positive is more crucial in cases like spam filtering or biometric authentication, where marking a legitimate item as positive creates bigger harm, such as missing important emails or allowing unauthorized access. A false negative is more crucial in cases like cancer diagnosis or fraud detection, where missing a real positive case can lead to severe consequences. So the importance depends on business impact and domain risk. In practice, we decide based on the cost of each error. The evaluation metric should align with that cost.\n",
    "\n",
    "Quick comparison table\n",
    "Scenario\tMore Crucial Error\tReason\n",
    "Spam detection\tFalse Positive\tImportant genuine mail may be lost\n",
    "Face unlock\tFalse Positive\tUnauthorized access possible\n",
    "Cancer detection\tFalse Negative\tReal disease may be missed\n",
    "Fraud detection\tFalse Negative\tFraudulent activity may pass\n",
    "One-line memory trick\n",
    "\n",
    "FP matters when false alarm is costly.\n",
    "FN matters when missing the real problem is costly."
   ]
  },
